	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />For some reason I'm thinking the FC only takes DC, while SNES/SFC/NES can take AC or DC.  I could be remembering totally wrong though, since I've never had an FC.  If it can't take AC or got fried from wrong polarity you could try replacing the regulator (7805) in there.
<br />
<br />You could also use a voltmeter between VCC/GND in there and see if it's got voltage when it's switched on.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


