	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Switch is probably OK, though I imagine you could test that with the multimeter.
<br />
<br />I would test the power at the voltage regulator (7805, 3-pin thing connected to a heatsink of some sort).  First pin (near the dot) is the input voltage, that should read as what the DC input is from the power adapter.  Middle pin is GND, 3rd pin is output voltage which should be around 5V.  If you get different results, put in a new 7805.  As far as the power supply, if the previous owner mis-used it the 7805 would be the first (and only?) thing to go.  Also check for damaged/exploded capacitors near the regulator.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
